HEADWORD: nonsectarian
<hw>nonsectarian</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>not restricted to one sect or
school or party; <as>as, religious training in a <ex>nonsectarian</ex>
atmosphere; public funding is restricted to <ex>nonsectarian</ex>
colleges</as>. Opposite of <ant>sectarian</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms:
<stype>ecumenic, oecumenic, ecumenical, oecumenical</stype>;
<stype>interchurch, interdenominational</stype>;
<stype>nondenominational</stype>; <stype>undenominational, unsectarian
</stype>]⟦br⟧
